since we all think we did it incorrectly i'll start by saying what i did: we know f(x) = d(x)q(x) + r(x) the least multiple of d(x) that is higher than f(x) is f(x)+d(x)-r(x) we know this because:
5 = (2)(2) + 1 Least multiple of 2 that is >5 is 6, which is 5+2-1 11 = (4)(2) + 3 Least multiple of 4 that is >11 is 12, which is 11+4-3 20 = (7)(2) + 6 Least multiple of 7 that is >20 is 21, which is 20+7-6
